'''''Samba in Berlin''''' ({{lang-pt|'''Samba em Berlim'''}}) is a 1943 Brazilian [[musical comedy film]] directed by [[Luiz de Barros]] and starring [[Mesquitinha]], [[Laura Suarez (singer)|Laura Suarez]] and [[Dercy Gonçalves]]. It is a [[World War II]] film part of the popular tradition of [[Chanchada|chanchadas]], aiming to poke fun at [[Nazi Germany]] with whom Brazil was now at war.<ref>Dennison & Shaw p.71–72</ref>

